-- Chilean Stocks: Concha & Toro, Copec, Hortifrut, Latam Airlines
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-07-12T22:00:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-12/chilean-stocks-concha-toro-copec-and-hortifrut-are-active.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa index  fell 0.2 percent to 4,355.89. The  MSCI Chile
index (MXCL)  dropped 0.5 percent to 2,405.53.  Empresas Copec SA (COPEC)   declined 1.1 percent to
7,194.2 pesos.  Chile ’s largest pulp exporter fell in line with
global equity markets on concern a faltering economic recovery
will hurt corporate profits.  Hortifrut SA (HF CI) fell 2.5 percent to 311.93 pesos. The
Chilean berries exporter sold 103.6 million shares today at 320
pesos in an initial public offering in Santiago, below its
initial 335-to-340 pesos target range.  Latam Airlines Group SA (LAN)   rose 0.8 percent to 12,505
pesos for its biggest increase in three weeks. Latin American
largest airline reported an 11.5 percent increase in passenger
traffic in June from a year earlier.  Vina Concha & Toro SA (CONCHA)   fell for a fourth day,
declining 1.3 percent to 955.01 pesos. Deutsche Bank AG reduced
its price estimate for Chile’s largest wine exporter to $46.25
per American depositary receipt after the company reported
second-quarter volumes. The ADRs fell 1.4 percent to $38.63.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
